# 7. Features Implemented

Several Postman features were implemented during the project.

## Environment Variables

Used to store reusable configuration values.

## Authorization

JWT Bearer authentication was configured for protected endpoints.

## Request Organization

Requests were grouped into logical folders based on application modules.

## Examples

Example responses were created to document expected API behavior.

## Mock Server

Mock responses were generated to simulate backend responses without requiring a running server.

## Flows

Basic Postman Flows were explored to automate request execution visually.

## Visualizer

The Visualizer feature was used to display JSON responses as formatted HTML tables inside Postman.

## Code Generation

Requests were converted into multiple programming languages including:

* cURL
* JavaScript
* Python
* Java
* PHP

This makes integration with client applications much faster.

